name: house
description: a building for human habitation, especially one that is lived in by a family or small group of people.; a building in which people meet for a particular activity; a religious community that occupies a particular building; a legislative or deliberative assembly; a style of popular dance music typically using synthesized drum and bass lines, sparse repetitive vocals, and a fast beat.; any of the twelve divisions of the celestial sphere, based on the positions of the ascendant and midheaven at a given time and place, and determined by any of a number of methods.

name: back
description: the rear surface of the human body from the shoulders to the hips; the side or part of something that is away from the spectator or from the direction in which it moves or faces; the rear; a player in a field game whose initial position is behind the front line
example: he lay on his back;back pain;Forbes slapped me on the back

name: old
description: having lived for a long time; no longer young; belonging only or chiefly to the past; former or previous; of a specified age; used to express affection, familiarity, or contempt
example: the old man lay propped up on cushions;he was fourteetn years old;a seven-month-old baby;it gets the old adrenaline going;“ Good old Mom,” she said

name: but
description: used to introduce a phrase or clause contrasting with what has already been mentioned; used to indicate the impossibility of anything other than what is being stated; used to introduce a response expressing a feeling such as surprise or anger; used after an expression of apology for what one is about to say; without it being the case that
example: one cannot but sympathize;there was nothing they could do but swallow their pride;they had no alternative but to follow;I'm sorry, but I can't pay you;it never rains but it pours

name: change
description: make or become different; take or use another instead of

name: again
description: another time; once more
example: it was great to meet old friends again;they were disappointed yet again

name: after
description: in the time following (an event or another period of time); behind; in pursuit or quest of; next to and following in order or importance; in allusion to (someone or something with the same or a related name); concerning or about
example: after a while he returned;shortly after Christmas;there's only one thing to do after an experience like that;she went out, shutting the door after her;in their order of priorities health comes after housing;x comes after y in the series;they named her Pauline, after Barbara's mother;she has asked after Iris's mother

name: which
description: asking for information specifying one or more people or things from a definite set
example: which are the best varieties of grapes for long keeping?;which of the suspects murdered him?;which way is the wind blowing?

name: land
description: the part of the earth's surface that is not covered by water, as opposed to the sea or the air; a country; the space between the rifling grooves in a gun.
example: the reptiles lay their eggs on land;after four weeks at sea we sighted land

name: look
description: direct one's gaze toward someone or something or in a specified direction; think of or regard in a specified way; have the appearance or give the impression of being; rely on to do or provide something

name: hot
description: having a high degree of heat or a high temperature; (of food) containing or consisting of pungent spices or peppers which produce a burning sensation when tasted; passionately enthusiastic, eager, or excited; involving much activity, debate, or intense feeling; knowledgeable or skillful; difficult to deal with
example: a very hot dish cooked with green chili;Tony is very hot on local history

name: ask
description: say something in order to obtain an answer or some information; request (someone) to do or give something; invite (someone) to one's home or a function
example: people are always asking questions;“How much further?” I asked;the old man asked about her job;he asked if she wanted coffee;he asked whether his electric wheelchair would fit through their doors;Mary asked her father for money;I asked him to call the manager;don't be afraid to ask for advice;it's about time we asked Pam to dinner

name: kind
description: a group of people or things having similar characteristics
example: all kinds of music;a new kind of education;more data of this kind would be valuable

name: play
description: engage in activity for enjoyment and recreation rather than a serious or practical purpose; take part in (a sport); represent (a character) in a theatrical performance or a film; perform on (a musical instrument); move lightly and quickly, so as to appear and disappear; flicker; allow (a fish) to exhaust itself pulling against a line before reeling it in.
example: she played Ophelia

name: before
description: during the period of time preceding (a particular event, date, or time); in front of; in preference to; with a higher priority than
example: she had to rest before dinner;the day before yesterday;they lived rough for four days before they were arrested;his playing days had ended six years before;it's never happened to me before;before the war;it wasn't long before I had my first bite;Matilda stood before her, panting;trotting through the city with guards running before and behind;the patterns swam before her eyes;a skilled warrior who places duty before all else;they would die before they would cooperate with each other

name: could
description: used to indicate possibility.; used in making polite requests.; used to indicate annoyance because of something that has not been done.
example: they could be right;could I use the phone?

name: call
description: give (an infant or animal) a specified name; cry out (a word or words); contact or attempt to contact (a person or number) by phone; order or request the attendance of; announce or decide that (an event, especially a meeting, strike, or election) is to happen; (of a person) pay a brief visit; (of an umpire or other official in a game) pronounce (a ball, stroke, or other action) to be the thing specified; cause (a subroutine) to be executed
example: they called their daughter Hannah;he heard an insistent voice calling his name;Meredith was already calling out a greeting;he had promised Celia he would call in at the clinic;he called around last night looking for you

name: start
description: come into being; begin or be reckoned from a particular point in time or space; cause (an event or process) to happen; give a small jump or make a sudden jerking movement from surprise or alarm
example: two men started the blaze that caused the explosion;those women started all the trouble

name: carry
description: support and move (someone or something) from one place to another; support the weight of; (of a sound, ball, missile, etc.) reach a certain point; assume or accept (responsibility or blame); have as a feature or consequence; approve (a proposed measure) by a majority of votes; transfer (a figure) to an adjacent column during an arithmetical operation (e.g., when a column of digits adds up to more than ten).
example: the bridge is capable of carrying even the heaviest loads;being a combat sport, karate carries with it the risk of injury;each bike carries a ten-year guarantee

name: country
description: a nation with its own government, occupying a particular territory; districts and small settlements outside large towns, cities, or the capital; an area or region with regard to its physical features
example: the country's increasingly precarious economic position;the airfield is right out in the country;a country lane;a tract of wild country

name: water
description: a colorless, transparent, odorless liquid that forms the seas, lakes, rivers, and rain and is the basis of the fluids of living organisms.; a stretch or area of water, such as a river, sea, or lake; urine; the amniotic fluid surrounding a fetus in the womb, especially as discharged in a flow shortly before birth; the quality of transparency and brilliance shown by a diamond or other gem.; capital stock that represents a book value greater than the true assets of a company.

name: late
description: doing something or taking place after the expected, proper, or usual time; belonging or taking place near the end of a particular time or period; (of a specified person) no longer alive
example: his late arrival;she was half an hour late for her lunch appointment;her late husband's grave;the late William Jennings Bryan

name: close
description: a short distance away or apart in space or time; denoting a family member who is part of a person's immediate family, typically a parent or sibling; (of observation, examination, etc.) done in a careful and thorough way; uncomfortably humid or airless
example: a close, hazy day;it was very close in the dressing room

name: school
description: an institution for educating children; any institution at which instruction is given in a particular discipline; a group of people, particularly writers, artists, or philosophers, sharing the same or similar ideas, methods, or style
example: Ryder's children did not go to school at all;school supplies;a dancing school;the Frankfurt school of critical theory

name: between
description: at, into, or across the space separating (two objects or regions); in the period separating (two points in time); in the interval separating (two points on a scale); indicating a connection or relationship involving two or more parties; by combining the resources or actions of (two or more people or other entities)
example: the border between Mexico and the United States;the dog crawled between us and lay down at our feet;those who travel by train between London and Paris;they snack between meals;the long, cold nights between autumn and spring;a man aged between 18 and 30;between 25 and 40 percent off children's clothes;the difference between income and expenditure;we have created something between us;oxygen and nitrogen between them account for 99 per cent of air

name: answer
description: a thing said, written, or done to deal with or as a reaction to a question, statement, or situation

name: learn

example: they'd started learning French;she is learning to play the piano;we learn from experience;“That'll learn you,” he chuckled;we'll have to learn you to milk cows

name: always
description: at all times; on all occasions; as a last resort; failing all else
example: the sun always rises in the east;if the marriage doesn't work out, we can always get divorced

name: feel
description: be aware of (a person or object) through touching or being touched.; experience (an emotion or sensation).
example: she felt someone touch her shoulder;I felt a sense of excitement;The film has a very gritty, realistic feel , again lifting it above being a merely stereotypical genre exercise.

name: dog
description: a domesticated carnivorous mammal that typically has a long snout, an acute sense of smell, nonretractable claws, and a barking, howling, or whining voice.; a person regarded as unpleasant, contemptible, or wicked (used as a term of abuse); a mechanical device for gripping.; feet
example: if only I could sit down and rest my tired dogs

name: enough
description: as much or as many as required
example: too much work and not enough people to do it;there was just enough room for two cars;getting enough of the right things to eat;there will be time enough to tell you when we meet;they ordered more than enough for five people

name: body
description: the physical structure of a person or an animal, including the bones, flesh, and organs; the main section of a car or aircraft; the main or central part of something, especially a building or text; a large or substantial amount of something; a mass or collection of something; a distinct material object; a full or substantial quality of flavor in wine.; (in pottery) a clay used for making the main part of ceramic ware, as distinct from a glaze.

name: decide
description: come to a resolution in the mind as a result of consideration

name: boat
description: a small vessel propelled on water by oars, sails, or an engine; a serving dish in the shape of a boat
example: a fishing boat;a boat trip;a gravy boat

name: area

name: base
description: the lowest part or edge of something, especially the part on which it rests or is supported; a conceptual structure or entity on which something draws or depends; a place used as a center of operations by the armed forces or others; a headquarters; a main or important element or ingredient to which other things are added; a substance capable of reacting with an acid to form a salt and water, or (more broadly) of accepting or neutralizing hydrogen ions.; the middle part of a bipolar transistor, separating the emitter from the collector.; the root or stem of a word or a derivative.; a number used as the basis of a numeration scale.; one of the four stations that must be reached in turn to score a run.

name: ship
description: a vessel larger than a boat for transporting people or goods by sea.

name: fire

name: feet
description: the lower extremity of the leg below the ankle, on which a person stands or walks.

name: complete

name: common
description: occurring, found, or done often; prevalent; shared by, coming from, or done by more than one; showing a lack of taste and refinement; vulgar.; (in Latin and certain other languages) of or denoting a gender of nouns that are conventionally regarded as masculine or feminine, contrasting with neuter.; (of a syllable) able to be either short or long.; (of a crime) of relatively minor importance

name: dry

name: hot
description: having a high degree of heat or a high temperature; (of food) containing or consisting of pungent spices or peppers which produce a burning sensation when tasted; passionately enthusiastic, eager, or excited; involving much activity, debate, or intense feeling; knowledgeable or skillful; difficult to deal with

name: clear

name: cold

Microscopic organisms typically consist of a single cell, which is either eukaryotic or prokaryotic.; a small group forming a nucleus of political activity, typically a secret, subversive one; a device containing electrodes immersed in an electrolyte, used for current-generation or electrolysis.; the local area covered by one of the short-range transmitters in a cellular telephone system.

name: moment
description: a very brief period of time; importance; a turning effect produced by a force acting at a distance on an object.; a quantity that expresses the average or expected value of the first, second, third, or fourth power of the deviation of each component of a frequency distribution from some given value, typically mean or zero. The first moment is the mean, the second moment the variance, the third moment the skew, and the fourth moment the kurtosis.

name: dress

name: held
description: grasp, carry, or support with one's arms or hands.

name: either

name: beat

name: sense

example: the bear has a keen sense of smell that enables it to hunt at dusk;she had the sense of being a political outsider;he earned respect by the good sense he showed at meetings;it is not clear which sense of the word “characters” is intended in this passage

name: bottom
description: the lowest point or part of something; a person's buttocks; one of six flavors of quark.; stamina or strength of character, especially of a horse.; a man who takes the passive role in anal intercourse with another man.; the second half of an inning
example: the bottom of the page;she paused at the bottom of the stairs;he climbs the side of the gorge, scratching his bottom unselfconsciously;the bottom of the ninth

name: spring
description: move or jump suddenly or rapidly upward or forward; originate or arise from; cushion or fit (a vehicle or item of furniture) with springs; (especially of wood) become warped or split.; pay for, especially as a treat for someone else
example: madness and creativity could spring from the same source;he's never offered to spring for dinner

name: century
description: a period of one hundred years; a score of one hundred in a sporting event, such as a cricket match.; a company in the ancient Roman army, originally of one hundred men.
example: a century ago most people walked to work

name: coast
description: the part of the land near the sea; the edge of the land; a run or movement in or on a vehicle without the use of power.
example: the west coast of Africa;they sailed further up the coast;the coast road

name: element
description: a part or aspect of something abstract, especially one that is essential or characteristic; each of more than one hundred substances that cannot be chemically interconverted or broken down into simpler substances and are primary constituents of matter. Each element is distinguished by its atomic number, i.e. the number of protons in the nuclei of its atoms.; the weather, especially strong winds, heavy rain, and other kinds of bad weather; a part in an electric teapot, heater, or stove that contains a wire through which an electric current is passed to provide heat.
example: the death had all the elements of a great tabloid story;there are four elements to the proposal;there was no barrier against the elements

name: cloud
description: a visible mass of condensed water vapor floating in the atmosphere, typically high above the ground; a state or cause of gloom, suspicion, trouble, or worry; a network of remote servers hosted on the Internet and used to store, manage, and process data in place of local servers or personal computers
example: the sun had disappeared behind a cloud;the full moon, hidden by veils of cloud;a black cloud hung over their lives;the only cloud to appear on the horizon was Leopold's unexpected illness;once you are logged in to your cloud storage space, you can upload files to it and share them with others;$13 per month gets you 25GB of storage in the cloud

name: bone
description: any of the pieces of hard whitish tissue making up the skeleton in humans and other vertebrates; the calcified material of which bones consist; the basic or essential framework of something; a penis.
example: his injuries included many broken bones;a shoulder bone

name: compare
description: estimate, measure, or note the similarity or dissimilarity between; form the comparative and superlative degrees of (an adjective or an adverb)
example: individual schools compared their facilities with those of others in the area;the survey compares prices in different countries;total attendance figures were 28,000, compared to 40,000 at last year's event;words of one syllable are usually compared by “-er” and “-est.”

name: meat
description: the flesh of an animal (especially a mammal) as food; food of any kind.
example: pieces of meat;place meat and poultry in the refrigerator immediately;meat sandwiches;assorted meats

name: print
description: produce (books, newspapers, magazines, etc.), especially in large quantities, by a mechanical process involving the transfer of text, images, or designs to paper; write (text) clearly without joining the letters; mark (a surface, typically a textile or a garment) with a colored design or pattern
example: print your name and address on the back of the check;it will be easier to read if I print

name: current
description: belonging to the present time; happening or being used or done now
example: keep abreast of current events;I started my current job last year

name: chord
description: a group of (typically three or more) notes sounded together, as a basis of harmony
example: the triumphal opening chords;a G major chord

name: bar
description: a long rod or rigid piece of wood, metal, or similar material, typically used as an obstruction, fastening, or weapon.; a counter across which alcoholic drinks or refreshments are served.; a barrier or restriction to an action or advance; a measure of music or the time of a piece of music.; a partition in a courtroom or legislative assembly, now usually notional, beyond which most people may not pass and, in court, at which an accused person stands; the legal profession.
example: political differences are not necessarily a bar to a good relationship

name: atom
description: the basic unit of a chemical element.

name: agree
description: have the same opinion about something; concur; consent to do something that has been suggested by another person; be consistent with
example: I completely agree with your recent editorial;we both agreed on issues such as tougher penalties for criminals;“Yes, it's dreadful, isn't it,” she agreed;I agree that consumers are always right;she had agreed to go and see a movie with him;your body language does not agree with what you are saying

name: depend
description: be controlled or determined by; rely on; hang down
example: differences in earnings depended on a wide variety of factors;the kind of person you could depend on;his tongue depended from open jaws

name: fresh
description: (of food) recently made or obtained; not canned, frozen, or otherwise preserved; not previously known or used; new or different; (of a person) full of energy and vigor; (of water) not salty; (of the wind) cool and fairly strong; (of a person) having just had (a particular experience) or come from (a particular place); presumptuous toward someone, especially in a sexual way; (of a cow) yielding a renewed or increased supply of milk following the birth of a calf.
example: fresh fruit;the court had heard fresh evidence;they are feeling fresh after a good night's sleep;all the fresh water in the world's lakes;a fresh northerly wind was speeding the ship southwards;we were fresh out of art school;one truck driver decided to get fresh with me

name: allow
description: give (someone) permission to do something; give the necessary time or opportunity for; admit the truth of; concede
example: the dissident was allowed to leave the country;they agreed to a ceasefire to allow talks with the government;he stopped for a moment to allow his eyes to adjust;my household duties were too many to allow of a visit to the hospital;he allowed that the penalty appeared too harsh for the crime;“Could happen,” she allowed indifferently

name: master
description: a man who has people working for him, especially servants or slaves; a man in charge of an organization or group.; a skilled practitioner of a particular art or activity; a person who holds a second or further degree from a university or other academic institution (only in titles and set expressions); used as a title prefixed to the name of a boy not old enough to be called “Mr.”; an original movie, recording, or document from which copies can be made
example: I'm a master of disguise;Master James Williams;the master tape

name: coat
description: an outer garment worn outdoors, having sleeves and typically extending below the hips; an animal's covering of fur or hair.; an outer layer or covering of a specified kind
example: a winter coat;his coat pocket;the protein coat of the virus

name: insect
description: a small arthropod animal that has six legs and generally one or two pairs of wings
example: insect pests

name: captain
description: the person in command of a ship.

name: create
description: bring (something) into existence
example: he created a thirty-acre lake;over 170 jobs were created

name: crowd
description: a large number of people gathered together in a disorganized or unruly way
example: a huge crowd gathered in the street outside

name: thin
description: having opposite surfaces or sides close together; of little thickness or depth; (of a person) having little, or too little, flesh or fat on their body; having few parts or members relative to the area covered or filled; sparse; containing much liquid and not much solid substance; too weak to justify a result or effect; inadequate
example: thin slices of bread;she was painfully thin;a depressingly thin crowd;his hair was going thin

name: arrive
description: reach a place at the end of a journey or a stage in a journey
example: we arrived at his house and knocked at the door;the team arrived in New Delhi on July 30;they had recently arrived from Turkey

name: division
description: the action of separating something into parts or the process of being separated; disagreement between two or more groups, typically producing tension or hostility; the process or skill of dividing one number by another.; each of the parts into which something is divided; a partition that divides two groups or things
example: the division of the land into small fields;a gene that helps regulate cell division;a growing sense of division between north and south;deep cultural divisions;the main divisions of the book

name: charge
description: demand (an amount) as a price from someone for a service rendered or goods supplied; accuse (someone) of something, especially an offense under law; entrust (someone) with a task as a duty or responsibility; store electrical energy in (a battery or battery-operated device); rush forward in attack; place a heraldic bearing on
example: the shaver can be charged up and used while traveling;a pennant argent, charged with a cross gules

name: danger
description: the possibility of suffering harm or injury
example: his life was in danger

name: climb
description: go or come up (a slope, incline, or staircase), especially by using the feet and sometimes the hands; ascend; move with effort, especially into or out of a confined space; clamber
example: we began to climb the hill;the air became colder as they climbed higher;he climbed up the steps slowly;Howard started to climb out of the front seat;I climbed down a narrow ladder;he climbed to a high bough

name: describe
description: give an account in words of (someone or something), including all the relevant characteristics, qualities, or events; mark out or draw (a geometric figure)
example: the man was described as tall, clean-shaven, and with short dark hair;on the diameter of a circle an equilateral triangle is described

name: burn
description: (of a fire) flame or glow while consuming a material such as coal or wood; be or cause to be destroyed by fire; be possessed by (a desire or an emotion); drive very fast; produce (a compact disc or DVD) by copying from an original or master copy.
example: a fire burned and crackled cheerfully in the grate;he watched his restaurant burn to the ground;Martha was burning with curiosity

name: consider
description: think carefully about (something), typically before making a decision
example: each application is considered on its merits

name: copy
description: a thing made to be similar or identical to another; a single specimen of a particular book, record, or other publication or issue; matter to be printed; a blank booklet or notebook used for schoolwork
example: the problem is telling which is the original document and which the copy;the record has sold more than a million copies;examinees will not be allowed to take pens, copies, or water bottles inside the test center;you need a stock of exercise copies, A4 refill pads, and maths copies

name: natural
description: existing in or caused by nature; not made or caused by humankind; of or in agreement with the character or makeup of, or circumstances surrounding, someone or something; (of a parent or child) related by blood; (of a note) not sharped or flatted; relating to earthly or unredeemed human or physical nature as distinct from the spiritual or supernatural realm.; (of a bid) straightforwardly reflecting one's holding of cards.
example: carrots contain a natural antiseptic that fights bacteria;natural disasters such as earthquakes;sharks have no natural enemies;such adopted children always knew who their natural parents were;the bassoon plays G-natural instead of A-flat

name: difficult
description: needing much effort or skill to accomplish, deal with, or understand
example: she had a difficult decision to make;the questions are too difficult for the children

name: corner
description: a place or angle where two or more sides or edges meet; a part, region, or area, especially one regarded as secluded or remote; each of the diagonally opposite ends of the ring, where a contestant rests between rounds.; each of the two parallel sides of home plate, which are perceived as defining the vertical edges of the strike zone.
example: Jan sat at one corner of the table;they descended on the college from all corners of the world;his wisdom was disseminated to the four corners of the earth;she couldn't bear journalists prying into every corner of her life

name: dear
description: regarded with deep affection; cherished by someone; expensive.
example: a dear friend;he is very dear to me

name: branch
description: a part of a tree which grows out from the trunk or from a bough.

name: afraid
description: feeling fear or anxiety; frightened
example: I'm afraid of dogs;she tried to think about the future without feeling afraid

name: apple
description: the round fruit of a tree of the rose family, which typically has thin red or green skin and crisp flesh. Many varieties have been developed as dessert or cooking fruit or for making cider.; the tree which bears apples.

name: feed
description: give food to; supply (a machine) with material, power, or other things necessary for its operation; supply water to (a body of water); insert further coins into (a meter) to extend the time for which it operates.; supply (someone) with (information, ideas, etc.); prompt (an actor) with (a line); (in ball games) pass (the ball) to a player; distribute (a broadcast) to local television or radio stations via satellite or network; cause to move gradually and steadily, typically through a confined space
example: the raiders fed the guard dog to keep it quiet;he fed her brownies he had just baked;the programs are fed into the computer;I think he is feeding his old employer commercial secrets;programs that the national networks feed to local stations;make holes through which to feed the cables

name: valley
description: a low area of land between hills or mountains, typically with a river or stream flowing through it; an internal angle formed by the intersecting planes of a roof, or by the slope of a roof and a wall.
example: the Thames Valley;the valley floor

name: block
description: a large solid piece of hard material, especially rock, stone, or wood, typically with flat surfaces on each side; a large single building subdivided into separate rooms, apartments, or offices; a large quantity or allocation of things regarded as a unit; an obstacle to the normal progress or functioning of something; a flat area of something, especially a solid area of color; a pulley or system of pulleys mounted in a case.; a person's head
example: a block of marble;substantial demands for time off may constitute a block to career advancement;an emotional block;“I'll knock your block off,” he said

name: company
description: a commercial business; the fact or condition of being with another or others, especially in a way that provides friendship and enjoyment; a number of individuals gathered together, especially for a particular purpose; the Central Intelligence Agency.
example: I could do with some company;the Mayor addressed the assembled company

name: cotton
description: a soft white fibrous substance that surrounds the seeds of a tropical and subtropical plant and is used as textile fiber and thread for sewing; the plant that is commercially grown for cotton products. Oil and a protein-rich flour are also obtained from the seeds.
example: a cargo of cotton and wheat;a white cotton blouse;an Indian hammock woven in colored cottons

name: column
description: an upright pillar, typically cylindrical and made of stone or concrete, supporting an entablature, arch, or other structure or standing alone as a monument.; a vertical division of a page or text.; one or more lines of people or vehicles moving in the same direction
example: a column of tanks moved northwest;we walked in a column

name: skill
description: the ability to do something well; expertise
example: difficult work, taking great skill

name: especially
description: used to single out one person, thing, or situation over all others; to a great extent; very much
example: he despised them all, especially Sylvester;a new song, written especially for Jonathan;he didn't especially like dancing;sleep is especially important for growing children

name: success
description: the accomplishment of an aim or purpose
example: the president had some success in restoring confidence

name: deal
description: distribute (cards) in an orderly rotation to players for a game or round; take part in commercial trading of a particular commodity; take measures concerning (someone or something), especially with the intention of putting something right; inflict (a blow) on (someone or something)

name: chief
description: a leader or ruler of a people or clan; an ordinary consisting of a broad horizontal band across the top of the shield.
example: the chief of the village;the Tlingit chief;an island where Chief Seattle was born

name: death
description: the action or fact of dying or being killed; the end of the life of a person or organism
example: an increase in deaths from skin cancer;I don't believe in life after death;a death sentence

name: born
description: existing as a result of birth.
example: he was born in Seattle;He was born to teach," says Julius, an assistant research scientist emeritus in the Department of Epidemiology.

name: continent
description: any of the world's main continuous expanses of land (Africa, Antarctica, Asia, Australia, Europe, North America, South America).

name: suffix
description: a morpheme added at the end of a word to form a derivative, e.g., -ation, -fy, -ing, -itis.

name: arrange
description: put (things) in a neat, attractive, or required order; organize or make plans for (a future event); adapt (a composition) for performance with instruments or voices other than those originally specified; settle (a dispute or claim)
example: she had just finished arranging the flowers;the columns are arranged in 12 rows;they hoped to arrange a meeting;my aunt arranged for the furniture to be stored;we've arranged the funeral for Saturday;songs arranged for viola and piano;the quarrel, partly by the interference of the Crown Prince, was arranged

name: determine
description: cause (something) to occur in a particular way; be the decisive factor in; ascertain or establish exactly, typically as a result of research or calculation; firmly decide; bring or come to an end.
example: it will be her mental attitude that determines her future;the point of our study was to determine what is true, not what is practicable;officials are working with state police to determine the cause of a deadly bus crash;he determined on a withdrawal of his forces;she determined to tackle Stephen the next day

name: broad
description: having an ample distance from side to side; wide; covering a large number and wide scope of subjects or areas; general; without detail; somewhat coarse and indecent; (of a regional accent) very noticeable and strong
example: a broad staircase;a broad range of experience;a broad outline of NATO's position;his broad Bronx accent

name: particular
description: used to single out an individual member of a specified group or class; especially great or intense; insisting that something should be correct or suitable in every detail; fastidious
example: the action seems to discriminate against a particular group of companies;when handling or checking cash the cashier should exercise particular care;she is very particular about cleanliness

name: camp
description: a place with temporary accommodations of huts, tents, or other structures, typically used by soldiers, refugees, prisoners, or travelers; the supporters of a particular party or doctrine regarded collectively
example: the enemy camp;a detention camp;the shot woke the whole camp;his views were firmly rooted in the conservative camp

name: claim
description: state or assert that something is the case, typically without providing evidence or proof
example: he claimed that he came from a wealthy, educated family;“I'm entitled to be conceited,” he claimed;these sunblocks claim protection factors as high as 34
